post2.title: MNIST Classificaton
post2.content: from sklearn.datasets import fetch_openml . mnist = fetch_openml('mnist_784', version=1) mnist.keys() . X, y = mnist["data"], mnist["target"] X.shape y.shape . import matplotlib as mpl import matplotlib.pyplot as plt some_digit = X[0] some_digit_image = some_digit.reshape(28, 28) plt.imshow(some_digit_image, cmap = mpl.cm.binary, interpolation="nearest") plt.axis("off") plt.show() .
